					<head>Midrashim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>A book of midrashic commentaries called Tsintsenet ha-man by Efraim ha-Darshan ben Gershon ha-Rofe.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="346v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tsintsenet ha-man </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">צנצנת המן</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Efraim ha-Darshan ben Gershon ha-Rofe</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">אפרים הדרשן בן גרשון הרופא</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Each derashah is preceded by a more or less lenghty reshut in rhyme. The discourses themselves are based on a small number of texts.</p>
							</note>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">בשנת <date calendar="Hebrew">ה'ד'ו'ר'</date> חברתי זה החבור.<locus n="2v"/>
							</incipit>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">זה הספר חיברתי אני <name type="person" role="author">אפרים בכ"ר גרשון הרופא</name> [...] וצנצנת המן קראתיהו [...] ובשנת <date calendar="Hebrew">ה'ט'ו'ר'</date> חבריהו וכו'.<locus n="346r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>346 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>202</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>346 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Irregular quires of 10 to 14 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Catchwords on every verso, mostly cut away.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="321v" to="346v"/>- written probably by the author (a partial autograph).</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Mutilated folios 346 and 347 are stuck together at the end of the manuscript.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="author">Efrayim ha-Darshan ben Gershon ha-Rofe</name>: inscribed, folio 346r.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mosheh ben Efrayim ha-Peruz</name>: inscribed in a note, folio 2r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
